<body>
<p>Reports <code>autowire</code> attributes in <code>&lt;bean&gt;</code> elements and suggests to explicitly inject bean properties if possible.</p>

<p><b>Example:</b></p>
<pre><code lang="java">
  public class MyComponent {
    public void setOtherBean(OtherBean bean){...}
  }
</code></pre>
<pre><code lang="xml">
  &lt;beans&gt;
    &lt;bean class="beans.OtherBean" id="bar"/&gt;
    &lt;bean autowire="byType" class="beans.MyComponent"/&gt;
    &lt;!-- "Unnecessary autowired dependency" --&gt;
    &lt;!-- suggests "Make autowired dependency explicit" --&gt;
  &lt;/beans&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>After applying the quick-fix:</p>

<pre><code lang="xml">
  &lt;beans&gt;
    &lt;bean class="beans.OtherBean" id="bar"/&gt;
    &lt;bean class="beans.MyComponent" id="foo"&gt;
      &lt;property name="otherBean" ref="otherBean"/&gt;
    &lt;/bean&gt;
  &lt;/beans&gt;
</code></pre>
</body>
</html>